						               													<description>This is a book game. Published as a book it includes multiple black &amp;amp; white and color maps. There are 3 games described, the Red, the Green and the Black game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Black game is a solo effort to see how long it takes and how accurate you can be with determining your map pinpoints.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Red game is meant for 4 players or fewer.  It is a game of chance and is won by the first person to reach the bombing target (the German city of Coblenz).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Green game is for any number of players, again as a game of chance but requires finding Pinpoints via Latitude and Longitude.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the Red and Green games a number of aircraft set off from their base in Kent to bomb a target at Coblenz.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The games requires the player to copy and create miniature airplanes, Compass Rose, 10 deg angle indicator and Latitude/Longitude Finder.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game includes maps as well as extensive briefing triggered by either a draw from a deck of cards or dice roll.  The players continue to roll/draw cards until they land on the target by exact count. Any overshooting requires the bomber to fly back around.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A briefing can have extensive instructions causing the player to head off track or be attacked by enemy fighters ending in a change of course and position on the map.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
